26/09/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The European Commission (EC) and the UNDP plan to jointly implement a training project for civil servants in BiH, it was announced on Friday (23 September). 
The EU will give 1m euros, while the UNDP will contribute 50,000 euros and training services. 
Also on Friday, the EC Delegation in BiH announced that it is providing an extra 200,000 euros to conduct IT and computer literacy courses for 700 civil servants there.
In other news Friday, a second Explosive Ordnance Disposal unit from BiH completed its training in advance of deployment in Iraq. 
It will rotate into the country in late November, when the first team's deployment ends. 
(Fena, PBS BiH, RTRS - 23/09/05)
